text: I am absolutely crushing it at work this week. Exhausted, but in a good way.
The workload is crushing me and I can't tell if I'm coping or just dissociating.
Today dragged on like wet cement. I finished my responsibilities, but everything felt heavy and muted. I wasn't sad exactlyâ€”just dim, like someone turned the saturation down on the world.
I didn't want to get out of bed, but I pushed myself through the day anyway. I guess I'm proud of that, even though I'm still tired to the bone.
Work was chaotic, deadlines everywhere, but somehow I thrived in it. My brain was humming, overstimulated maybe, but alive in a way I haven't felt in months.
I spent the evening watching the sunset in silence. The sky burned pink, orange, then blue. I felt present for onceâ€”not happy, not sadâ€”just here.
My thoughts drip slow like honeyâ€”sweet, but too heavy to swallow. I am grateful, yet tired of carrying myself.
I laughed with the rain todayâ€”it fell hard and wild and I felt alive beneath it.
A quiet ache hums in my spine. Nothing is wrong, but something isn't right. I sit with it anyway.
My heart claws like an animal against tomorrow, restless and afraid.
The stars were kind tonightâ€”they reminded me to breathe. A small miracle.

Everyone keeps telling me I'm doing great, but I feel like I'm barely hanging on.

I'm quietly proud of myself for not spiraling this time.
